.START 

LIFETIME CORP., Boston, sold 1.8 million common shares for $18.50 apiece.
The company said proceeds will be used to repay a portion of debt incurred primarily in connection with the August acquisition of American Service Bureau Inc. Proceeds will also be used to buy remaining equity in Office Angels Ltd. and for general purposes.
Salomon Brothers Inc. and Prudential-Bache Capital Funding co-managed the offering. 

